WEBVTT

00:11.177 --> 00:12.762
{\an8}████████████████████████████████

00:11.177 --> 00:12.762
♪ WE ARE RIDERS ON A MISSION ♪

00:12.846 --> 00:17.600
♪ ACTION KIDS
IN PLAY POSITION. ♪

00:34.117 --> 00:36.953
♪ WE ARE RIDERS ON A MISSION ♪

00:37.036 --> 00:40.206
♪ ACTION KIDS
IN FUN CONDITION. ♪

00:40.290 --> 00:42.041
PREPARE TO COUNT DOWN.

00:42.125 --> 00:44.961
[Captioning sponsored by THE
U.S. DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION

00:45.044 --> 00:46.796
and NICKELODEON]

01:03.313 --> 01:04.980
PARTY WAVE!

01:05.063 --> 01:05.648
YAHOO!

01:05.732 --> 01:08.318
HEADS UP, ROCKET BOY.

01:12.155 --> 01:14.741
HEY, WHERE DID EVERYBODY GO?

01:14.824 --> 01:16.326
(<i> grunts</i> )

01:16.409 --> 01:16.910
(<i> kids laughing</i> )

01:16.993 --> 01:17.786
(<i> static crackling</i> )

01:17.869 --> 01:21.456
HOW AWESOME WAS
THAT WIPEOUT, RAYMUNDO?

01:21.539 --> 01:22.290
DIDN'T
THAT HURT?

01:22.373 --> 01:23.792
{\an1}WHAT?

01:23.875 --> 01:26.753
DIDN'T YOU SEE THAT
SPECTACULAR NOSE RIDE?

01:26.836 --> 01:29.130
Tito:
REMINDS ME OF A HOOD ORNAMENT.

01:29.214 --> 01:31.466
MAN, WHAT A DAY THAT WAS.

01:31.549 --> 01:33.676
SURF'S LOOKING
PRETTY GOOD RIGHT NOW, DAD.

01:33.760 --> 01:37.013
ROCKET BOYS TO THE RESCUE.

01:37.096 --> 01:37.764
AH, I CAN'T.

01:37.847 --> 01:39.140
IT'S KIND OF BUSY HERE.

01:44.437 --> 01:45.313
(<i> squawks</i> )

01:47.232 --> 01:48.191
COME ON, DAD.

01:48.274 --> 01:50.443
ROCKET FAMILY
PARTY WAVE.

01:50.527 --> 01:51.528
(<i> all urging him on</i> )

01:51.611 --> 01:53.154
I DON'T KNOW.

01:53.238 --> 01:54.656
I GUESS MAYBE.

01:54.739 --> 01:56.199
TITO, CAN YOU
HANDLE IT?

01:56.282 --> 01:56.699
{\an1}YEAH!

01:56.783 --> 01:58.535
TITO CAN
HANDLE IT.

01:58.618 --> 01:59.619
YEAH, COME ON,
TITO

01:59.702 --> 02:01.287
YOU CAN DO IT.

02:01.371 --> 02:01.955
YOU DON'T MIND, DO YOU?

02:02.038 --> 02:04.791
ACTUALLY, I NEED A GOOD SURF.

02:04.874 --> 02:06.543
I'VE WORKED
67 DAYS STRAIGHT WITHOUT...

02:06.626 --> 02:07.585
(<i> kids chatting</i> )

02:07.669 --> 02:08.711
Reggie::
BYE, TITO!

02:08.794 --> 02:10.880
Twister:
SEE YOU LATER.

02:10.964 --> 02:13.174
(<i> quietly</i> ):
UH, THANKS, BRO.

02:13.258 --> 02:14.133
YEAH, RIGHT.

02:24.143 --> 02:27.230
{\an5}Otto:
MAN, THAT WAS THE BEST
WAVE SESSION ALL WEEK.

02:28.481 --> 02:31.234
NO, BRO, I THINK
YOU MEAN ALL YEAR.

02:31.317 --> 02:32.944
AND THAT LAST
RIDE, REGGIE

02:33.027 --> 02:34.404
{\an5}I THOUGHT YOU
WERE GOING TO BE
TUBED FOREVER.

02:34.487 --> 02:37.198
YEAH, I...

02:38.491 --> 02:41.578
{\an1}I THINK THIS BURGER
HAS BRUSSELS SPROUTS.

02:41.661 --> 02:42.579
EW.

02:42.662 --> 02:44.330
AND LOOK AT THIS.

02:44.414 --> 02:46.082
MY CORN ON THE COB'S
JUST...

02:46.165 --> 02:47.917
COB.

02:48.001 --> 02:50.253
{\an1}THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH MY MILKSHAKE.

02:50.336 --> 02:50.962
(<i> slurps</i> )

02:51.045 --> 02:54.257
SAM, THIS MILKSHAKE'S
SOLID SYRUP.

02:56.009 --> 02:58.678
WHATEVER.

02:58.761 --> 03:00.096
YES!

03:00.179 --> 03:01.389
AND THESE FRIES
ARE STILL FROZEN.

03:02.849 --> 03:04.684
(<i> crunches loudly</i> )

03:04.767 --> 03:06.102
MMM.

03:06.185 --> 03:07.145
NOT BAD, THOUGH.

03:07.228 --> 03:10.690
♪ MY ISLAND HOME CALLS ME... ♪

03:10.773 --> 03:12.191
(<i> rings bell</i> )

03:12.275 --> 03:14.819
(<i> Tito singing softly</i>
<i>and sadly</i> )

03:14.903 --> 03:17.864
{\an1}WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH TITO?

03:17.947 --> 03:21.284
♪ I WANT TO BE... ♪

03:21.367 --> 03:25.121
I'VE HEARD OF REVENGE,
BUT THIS HEINOUS.

03:25.204 --> 03:27.206
{\an5}HE'S BEEN
OUT OF SYNC
FOR DAYS NOW.

03:32.962 --> 03:34.839
{\an5}Otto:
I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT YOU GUYS

03:34.923 --> 03:37.592
BUT I NEED SOME GRINDAGE
THAT'S ACTUALLY GRINDABLE.

03:37.675 --> 03:38.968
LET'S HIT THE BOARDWALK.

03:39.886 --> 03:41.304
I'M BRINGING THESE FRIES.

03:41.387 --> 03:42.680
THEY'RE GOOD ON A HOT DAY.

03:42.764 --> 03:45.308
UM, I GOT SOME
STUFF TO DO.

03:45.391 --> 03:46.267
YOU GUYS GO AHEAD.

03:52.190 --> 03:55.735
HEY, RAYMUNDO,
I'M TAKING OFF FOR THE DAY.

03:55.818 --> 03:55.985
{\an1}ALOHA.

03:56.069 --> 03:57.570
WHAT?

03:57.654 --> 03:59.489
I MEAN, SURE,
IF YOU GOT TO

03:59.572 --> 04:03.034
{\an4}THOUGH, I HAVEN'T
MANNED THE GRILL
FOR A WHILE.

04:03.117 --> 04:04.744
(<i> tersely</i> ):
IT'S EASY--

04:04.827 --> 04:06.371
YOU PUT THINGS
ON IT

04:06.454 --> 04:07.330
THEY GET HOT

04:07.413 --> 04:08.623
THEN YOU
TAKE THEM OFF.

04:10.416 --> 04:12.168
HEY, TITO, HOW'S IT GOING?

04:13.461 --> 04:17.589
AS THE ANCIENT HAWAIIANS SAY,
SOMETIMES THE BIRD SINGS

04:17.673 --> 04:19.550
SOMETIMES IT
COUGHS UP A WORM.

04:21.636 --> 04:23.137
DAD, THIS IS TOO WEIRD.

04:23.221 --> 04:24.263
{\an1}WE HAVE TO
FIGURE THIS OUT.

04:26.432 --> 04:27.600
WELL, COME ON, MERV.

04:27.684 --> 04:29.686
A LITTLE BEACH FOOD
WON'T HURT YOU.

04:29.769 --> 04:30.520
YES, BUT HERE?

04:30.603 --> 04:33.147
WHO KNOWS WHAT GOES ON
IN THAT KITCHEN?

04:33.231 --> 04:36.192
WANT TO FIND OUT
FOR YOURSELF, MERV?

04:36.275 --> 04:36.359
WHA?!

04:38.861 --> 04:40.822
{\an1}WE'VE GOT A LITTLE
EMERGENCY HERE, VIOLET.

04:40.905 --> 04:42.740
CAN YOU COVER ME?

04:42.824 --> 04:45.201
EMERGENCY'S MY MIDDLE NAME.

04:45.284 --> 04:46.536
OF COURSE I'LL HELP OUT.

04:46.619 --> 04:47.161
I HOPE IT'S NOT SERIOUS.

04:47.245 --> 04:50.206
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT SERIOUS.

04:50.289 --> 04:53.293
{\an1}OH, MERV, IT'S GOOD TO
HELP OUT ONCE IN A WHILE.

04:54.460 --> 04:57.672
LET'S PLAY WITH
THE DEEP-FAT FRYER.

04:57.755 --> 05:00.258
MMM.

05:00.341 --> 05:01.718
{\an1}THE STIMPLETONS CAN
WATCH THE SHACK.

05:01.801 --> 05:03.761
WE'LL WATCH TITO.

05:06.389 --> 05:07.974
(<i> oil bubbling</i> )

05:11.269 --> 05:14.397
{\an5}Reggie:
HE LOOKS KIND
OF BLECH.

05:14.480 --> 05:15.356
OOH.

05:14.480 --> 05:15.356
OOH.

05:15.440 --> 05:16.899
{\an1}WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH HIM, DAD?

05:16.983 --> 05:17.692
{\an1}IT'S LIKE HE
DOESN'T EVEN CARE

05:17.775 --> 05:19.694
HE'S GETTING WHOMPED.

05:19.777 --> 05:23.197
(<i> groans</i> )

05:23.281 --> 05:24.073
MAN, HE'S OUT OF WHACK.

05:24.157 --> 05:30.580
(<i> sadly</i> ):
♪ I WANT TO BE ♪

05:30.663 --> 05:35.168
♪ IN HAWAII... ♪

05:41.299 --> 05:42.175
WHERE'S MY DAD?

05:42.258 --> 05:43.426
HAVE NO FEAR, OTTO.

05:43.509 --> 05:45.470
{\an1}MERV AND I ARE
MANNING THE FORT.

05:45.553 --> 05:47.221
THIS HOLE SHOULD BE CONDEMNED.

05:47.305 --> 05:50.224
SOMEBODY'S GOT TO
WHIP THIS PIT INTO SHAPE.

05:50.308 --> 05:51.976
{\an1}HANDS OFF
MY COUNTER, KID.

05:52.060 --> 05:53.978
(<i> Reggie and Ray panting</i> )

05:54.062 --> 05:56.355
WE NEED TO HAVE
AN EMERGENCY MEETING.

05:56.439 --> 05:57.231
THEN TAKE IT OUTSIDE!

05:57.315 --> 06:00.568
THE COUNTER'S FOR
PAYING CUSTOMERS ONLY.

06:03.654 --> 06:04.947
OKAY, HERE'S THE SCOOP:

06:05.031 --> 06:06.532
{\an1}TITO, OUR
OLDEST FRIEND

06:06.616 --> 06:07.283
AND ALL-AROUND GOOD GUY

06:07.366 --> 06:10.119
{\an1}IS FEELING LEFT OUT
AND HOMESICK.

06:10.203 --> 06:11.579
REALLY?

06:11.662 --> 06:13.247
I RELATE-- I'M
SICK OF MY HOME.

06:13.331 --> 06:16.084
NO, DORK, HE MISSES HIS FAMILY.

06:16.167 --> 06:17.627
THINK OF IT, YOU GUYS.

06:17.710 --> 06:19.170
HE GREW UP IN HAWAII--
A TROPICAL PARADISE

06:19.253 --> 06:22.632
AND MOST OF HIS FAMILY
IS STILL BACK THERE.

06:22.715 --> 06:23.758
{\an5}PEOPLE THAT
REALLY CARE
ABOUT HIM.

06:23.841 --> 06:25.718
WE NEED TO
SHOW HIM

06:25.802 --> 06:26.719
THAT WE
REALLY CARE.

06:26.803 --> 06:28.513
HE'S ALWAYS DOING STUFF FOR US

06:28.596 --> 06:29.806
BUT WE NEVER THANK HIM
OR ANYTHING.

06:29.889 --> 06:32.558
I THANKED HIM...

06:32.642 --> 06:34.560
ONCE... I THINK.

06:34.644 --> 06:35.061
I DEFINITELY DID...

06:35.144 --> 06:37.355
UNLESS I DREAMED IT.

06:37.438 --> 06:40.858
{\an5}LET'S SHOW TITO HE'S AN
IMPORTANT PART OF OUR FAMILY.

06:40.942 --> 06:42.318
{\an1}YEAH, HE'S
THE GUY WHO COOKS.

06:42.401 --> 06:43.986
HE'S STILL GOING
TO MISS HAWAII.

06:44.070 --> 06:44.821
MAYBE WE COULD
SEND HIM THERE.

06:44.904 --> 06:47.031
WE CAN'T AFFORD THAT.

06:47.115 --> 06:48.866
{\an5}BUT WE COULD BRING
A LITTLE OF HAWAII

06:48.950 --> 06:50.660
TO OCEAN SHORES
AS A BIG THANK YOU.

06:50.743 --> 06:52.954
HOW?

06:53.037 --> 06:55.623
LEAVE THAT TO ME.

06:55.706 --> 06:56.833
YOU GUYS READY?

06:56.916 --> 06:59.669
LET OPERATION TITO COMMENCE!

06:59.752 --> 07:01.796
All:
WOOGEDY-WOOGEDY-WOOGEDY-WOOGEDY!

07:05.049 --> 07:06.175
TITO, I GOT A PROBLEM

07:06.259 --> 07:08.469
AND YOU'RE THE ONLY
ONE WHO CAN HELP.

07:11.931 --> 07:14.016
WHOA... OW!

07:14.100 --> 07:17.019
YOU MUST NOT FIGHT
THE FORCES OF GRAVITY.

07:17.103 --> 07:18.479
FIND YOUR BALANCE.

07:19.939 --> 07:21.858
WHOA... WHOA!

07:21.941 --> 07:24.443
WHOO-HOO!

07:24.527 --> 07:25.736
ALL RIGHT!

07:25.820 --> 07:27.446
TITO!

07:27.530 --> 07:29.532
I COULDN'T DO IT
WITHOUT YOU, BRO.

07:29.615 --> 07:31.826
AH, THE ANCIENT HAWAIIANS SAY

07:31.909 --> 07:36.038
SOMETIMES IT'S BEST TO TRUST
THE WEIGHT OF EXPERIENCE.

07:36.122 --> 07:37.123
(<i> chuckles</i> )

07:37.206 --> 07:40.251
AND I GOT PLENTY OF EXPERIENCE.

07:42.003 --> 07:45.339
(<i> grunting</i> )

07:45.423 --> 07:46.799
COME ON, KITE.

07:46.883 --> 07:48.885
{\an1}ANCIENT HAWAIIANS
HAD A SAYING--

07:48.968 --> 07:50.678
FLY THE KITE;
IT MUST NOT FLY YOU.

07:50.761 --> 07:52.388
(<i> kite whistles out of sky</i> )

07:55.474 --> 07:59.395
I'M STARTING TO GET
REALLY MAD OVER HERE.

07:59.478 --> 08:02.023
Man:
GET OUT OF HERE, GUYS.

08:02.106 --> 08:04.317
SHE'S AS TOUGH AS NAILS.

08:04.400 --> 08:07.486
(<i> Tito humming to himself</i> )

08:09.488 --> 08:10.656
Twister:
UH, HEY, TITO?

08:10.740 --> 08:12.200
I THOUGHT YOU
COULD HELP ME

08:12.283 --> 08:13.534
WITH MY LONG DIVISION.

08:13.618 --> 08:17.663
I MEAN, SINCE I APPRECIATE YOU
AND EVERYTHING.

08:17.747 --> 08:18.664
{\an1}COME ON IN,
LITTLE TWISTER.

08:23.127 --> 08:24.086
IN MATHEMATICS...

08:24.170 --> 08:26.756
{\an1}YOU CARRY OVER
THE NUMBER

08:26.839 --> 08:29.425
{\an5}LIKE YOU CARRY
AN INJURED PIG
OVER THE HILL.

08:29.508 --> 08:30.426
SO THINK PIG.

08:30.509 --> 08:31.969
(<i> confused</i> ):
RIGHT.

08:35.097 --> 08:37.600
DID I MENTION I APPRECIATE YOU?

08:40.561 --> 08:42.438
(<i> strumming ukulele</i> )

08:42.520 --> 08:43.438
{\an1}HEY, TITO.

08:43.522 --> 08:44.190
{\an1}GOT A SEC?

08:44.273 --> 08:45.233
FOR YOU, I HAVE

08:45.316 --> 08:46.651
A LIFETIME OF SECONDS,
LITTLE REGGIE.

08:46.734 --> 08:50.738
I'VE GOT TO DO A REPORT ON
SPECIAL PLACES IN OCEAN SHORES

08:50.821 --> 08:53.115
AND CAN'T DECIDE
WHICH SPOT TO WRITE ABOUT.

08:53.199 --> 08:54.200
LIKE RIGHT HERE--

08:54.283 --> 08:56.285
{\an1}YOU CAUGHT HUMUNGO
HERE, RIGHT?

08:56.369 --> 08:58.663
AH, THAT WAS A DAY.

09:00.957 --> 09:02.625
Kids:
ALL RIGHT, COME ON, TITO!

09:02.708 --> 09:03.125
ALL RIGHT, TITO!

09:03.209 --> 09:05.628
YEAH, CHECK IT OUT!

09:05.711 --> 09:07.129
HE'S A MEAN ONE---

09:07.213 --> 09:10.633
BIG, MISTER NASTY FISH,
TERROR OF THE DEEP.

09:13.135 --> 09:15.888
(<i> all laughing</i> )

09:15.972 --> 09:19.850
{\an5}Tito:
I STILL SAY THAT LITTLE GUY
WAS VERY MUSCULAR.

09:19.934 --> 09:21.978
{\an1}HEY, THERE ARE A BUNCH
OF OTHER PLACES

09:22.061 --> 09:23.312
{\an1}I COULD
WRITE ABOUT, TOO.

09:23.396 --> 09:25.439
COME ON.

09:28.234 --> 09:29.485
SO, TELL ME, REGGIE

09:29.568 --> 09:30.903
WHAT DO YOU THINK OF

09:30.987 --> 09:32.780
WHEN YOU SEE THE WATER?

09:32.863 --> 09:34.240
I THINK OF A SPECIAL DAY

09:34.323 --> 09:35.574
AT LEAST IT WAS SPECIAL TO ME.

09:42.164 --> 09:44.041
YES! I'M DOING IT!

09:44.125 --> 09:46.627
I'M ACTUALLY SURFING!

09:46.711 --> 09:47.753
WHOA!

09:56.387 --> 09:58.597
{\an1}YOU KNOW,
IN EVERY FAMILY

09:58.681 --> 10:01.100
{\an1}I GUESS THERE'S
A MOM OR DAD

10:01.183 --> 10:02.643
OR A SISTER OR BROTHER

10:02.727 --> 10:05.021
BUT FOR AS LONG
AS I CAN REMEMBER

10:05.104 --> 10:06.897
I'VE HAD SOMETHING EXTRA.

10:06.981 --> 10:08.357
I HAVE A TITO.

10:08.441 --> 10:11.485
AND I HAVE A REGGIE.

10:11.569 --> 10:13.529
HEY, LET'S HIT THE SHACK.

10:13.612 --> 10:14.864
IT'S DINNERTIME.

10:21.287 --> 10:24.081
(<i> wood splintering</i> )

10:32.256 --> 10:34.884
All:
SURPRISE!

10:34.967 --> 10:36.218
(<i> screams</i> )

10:36.302 --> 10:37.428
(<i> laughing</i> ):
WHAT'S THIS?

10:37.511 --> 10:41.015
REGGIE! OTTO!
IS ALL THIS FOR ME?

10:41.098 --> 10:43.601
(<i> tropical drum beating softly</i> )

10:43.684 --> 10:47.480
(<i> playing lively music</i> )

10:47.563 --> 10:48.064
HERBIE, MOLEY AND ALBERT!

10:48.147 --> 10:51.233
HOW DID YOU GET HERE?

10:51.317 --> 10:52.401
THEY CAME
ALL THE WAY

10:52.485 --> 10:54.195
FROM PINEAPPLE
COUNTY, HAWAII

10:54.278 --> 10:56.530
TO PUT ON A SHOW FOR
THEIR NUMERO UNO CUZ.

10:56.614 --> 10:58.032
{\an1}WE KNEW YOU WERE
HOMESICK

10:58.115 --> 10:59.825
AND WE WANTED
TO DO SOMETHING.

10:59.909 --> 11:01.327
{\an1}SO WE PUT OUR
HEADS TOGETHER...

11:01.410 --> 11:04.872
AND NOW YOU CAN
GO HAWAII CRAZY.

11:07.458 --> 11:10.086
THIS MEANS SO MUCH.

11:10.169 --> 11:13.839
IN HAWAII, YOU KNOW,
A FAMILY IS CALLED <i> OHANA.</i>

11:13.923 --> 11:16.300
NEVER AGAIN AM I GOING TO FORGET

11:16.384 --> 11:20.179
I GOT ONE SPLENDID <i> OHANA</i>
RIGHT HERE IN OCEAN SHORES.

11:20.262 --> 11:24.266
(<i> all cheering</i> )

11:24.350 --> 11:27.603
(<i> playing lively music</i> )

11:27.686 --> 11:29.688
(<i> Tito laughs</i> )

11:42.368 --> 11:45.663
(<i> Tito babbling excitedly</i> )

12:05.808 --> 12:07.893
(<i> boy grunting</i> )

12:11.897 --> 12:12.356
Sam:
COME ON, ARNOLD.

12:12.440 --> 12:15.526
30 SECONDS TO HIGH TIDE.

12:16.694 --> 12:19.822
(<i> grunting furiously</i> )

12:19.905 --> 12:21.949
DUDE, EASY ON THE CAMERA!

12:23.492 --> 12:25.286
HUSTLE, PEOPLE.

12:26.579 --> 12:27.872
NOT BAD, GUYS.

12:30.791 --> 12:31.667
SHORE BREAK!

12:31.750 --> 12:33.294
RED ALERT!
HERE IT COMES!

12:41.302 --> 12:43.345
(<i> all cheering</i> )

12:43.429 --> 12:43.804
Otto:
THAT WAS AWESOME!

12:51.687 --> 12:54.356
CAREFUL, HONEY,
YOU'LL BURN YOURSELF.

12:54.440 --> 12:57.526
I KNOW HOW TO EAT PIZZA, MOTHER.

12:57.610 --> 12:58.569
(<i> sizzling</i> )

12:58.652 --> 12:59.737
OW!

13:00.237 --> 13:03.657
(<i> groaning</i> )

13:03.741 --> 13:04.617
(<i> no voice</i> )

13:04.700 --> 13:07.369
OH, IT LOOKS LIKE
WE'RE PART OF A SHOW.

13:07.453 --> 13:10.539
(<i> both laughing</i> )

13:13.667 --> 13:14.543
CAN IT, CLOWN!

13:14.627 --> 13:16.587
{\an1}THIS PLAY
STINKS ON ICE!

13:16.670 --> 13:18.047
OH!

13:18.130 --> 13:19.215
(<i> yelling</i> )

13:19.298 --> 13:21.884
SO, YOU <i> CAN</i> TALK, HUH?

13:21.967 --> 13:22.927
{\an1}LET'S SEE
IF YOU CAN SCREAM.

13:29.850 --> 13:31.685
MACKENZIE!

13:31.769 --> 13:32.978
{\an1}HONEY...

13:35.606 --> 13:36.899
(<i> cries out</i> )

13:36.982 --> 13:39.527
(<i> making Tarzan yell</i> )

13:39.610 --> 13:40.819
MACKENZIE!

13:40.903 --> 13:41.779
HONEY!

13:41.862 --> 13:41.946
MACKENZIE!

13:44.907 --> 13:46.575
MACKENZIE!

14:04.635 --> 14:05.678
RED ALERT!

14:05.761 --> 14:07.471
SPONGEHEAD AT 2:00!

14:07.555 --> 14:11.183
OH, NO, HE'S NOT GOING TO...

14:11.267 --> 14:13.269
OH, YEAH, HE'S GOING TO.

14:13.352 --> 14:15.145
INCOMING!

14:17.648 --> 14:18.566
(<i> yelling</i> )

14:18.649 --> 14:18.899
(<i> groans</i> )

14:23.195 --> 14:24.822
WAHOO?

14:25.906 --> 14:27.575
{\an1}YOU TOOK OUT
THE RETAINING WALL

14:27.658 --> 14:29.451
{\an1}AND HALF OF
THE REFLECTING POOL.

14:29.535 --> 14:31.829
(<i> chuckling</i> ):
COOL.

14:36.417 --> 14:36.834
{\an1}OFFICER!

14:36.917 --> 14:38.502
YOU'VE GOT TO HELP US!

14:38.586 --> 14:39.795
OUR DAUGHTER IS LOST!

14:39.878 --> 14:41.046
LOST CHILD?

14:41.130 --> 14:42.923
I'LL PUT AN ALL-POINTS BULLETIN
OUT RIGHT NOW.

14:46.927 --> 14:47.970
WE'LL PROBABLY NEED

14:48.053 --> 14:49.763
ABOUT 20 MORE
CUBIC FEET OF...

14:49.847 --> 14:51.849
SAN...D!

14:53.183 --> 14:54.727
WHERE'S MY MOMMY?

14:54.810 --> 14:56.562
MACKENZIE!

14:56.645 --> 14:59.815
{\an1}SAY IT, DON'T SPRAY IT,
LAME-O!

14:59.898 --> 15:01.483
(<i> whimpers</i> )

15:02.276 --> 15:05.446
RELAX, SAM, SHE'S
ONLY FIVE YEARS OLD.

15:05.529 --> 15:07.865
{\an1}TELL THAT TO EDDIE,
PRINCE OF THE NETHERWORLD.

15:07.948 --> 15:10.409
SHE TURNED HIM INTO
EDDIE, KING OF THE BLOODY NOSE.

15:10.492 --> 15:12.995
PROTECT YOURSELF, SQUID.

15:13.078 --> 15:13.996
ECH.

15:14.079 --> 15:15.831
LET <i> ME</i> HANDLE THIS, GUYS.

15:15.914 --> 15:17.291
HIYA, MACKENZIE.

15:17.374 --> 15:19.168
DO YOU LIKE
OUR BIG SAND CASTLE?

15:23.714 --> 15:24.256
UM...

15:24.340 --> 15:26.300
NO.

15:28.385 --> 15:30.262
SHE HAS A 'TUDE PROBLEM.

15:30.346 --> 15:31.513
D'OH!

15:35.017 --> 15:36.143
EXCUSE ME.

15:38.145 --> 15:38.437
GIVE ME FIVE!

15:38.520 --> 15:41.690
UH... OKAY.

15:42.775 --> 15:44.234
(<i> yelling</i> )

15:44.318 --> 15:45.277
OH...

15:45.361 --> 15:47.363
THAT'S FIVE.

15:47.446 --> 15:48.447
DEFINITELY.

15:48.530 --> 15:49.948
OH, THAT'S
GOT TO HURT!

15:51.909 --> 15:53.202
EXCUSE ME, MA'AM.

15:53.285 --> 15:55.204
HAVE YOU SEEN
THIS CHILD?

15:55.287 --> 15:57.956
SIR? WE'RE LOOKING
FOR OUR DAUGHTER.

15:58.040 --> 15:58.624
WE'VE LOST HER,
SHE'S ABOUT...

15:58.707 --> 16:01.210
I WAS OVER
BY THE BOARDWALK...

16:01.293 --> 16:02.044
LITTLE GIRL, PIGTAILS.

16:05.673 --> 16:08.217
{\an5}WE BETTER FIND
YOUR PARENTS,
MACKENZIE, OKAY?

16:08.300 --> 16:12.096
I DON'T KNOW WHERE THEY ARE!

16:12.179 --> 16:13.514
ARE YOU LOST?

16:13.597 --> 16:17.393
I'M LOST, AND I WANT MY MOMMY.

16:17.476 --> 16:20.437
(<i> shrieking</i> )

16:20.521 --> 16:21.730
OH, MAN, TAKE IT EASY.

16:21.814 --> 16:22.564
WE'LL FIND THEM,
DON'T WORRY.

16:22.648 --> 16:25.317
(<i> whimpering</i> )

16:26.568 --> 16:28.028
EVERYTHING'S
GOING TO BE FINE.

16:28.112 --> 16:29.530
{\an5}SURE!
ME AND REG
WILL GO

16:29.613 --> 16:31.740
TO THE LIFEGUARD
AND GET HELP.

16:31.824 --> 16:33.742
TWISTER AND SAM
WILL BE YOUR BUDDIES

16:33.826 --> 16:35.202
TILL WE BRING BACK
YOUR PARENTS, OKAY?

16:37.162 --> 16:38.163
{\an5}NO WAY!

16:37.162 --> 16:38.163
NO WAY!

16:38.247 --> 16:39.248
{\an1}BETTER BE NICE,
TWIST

16:39.331 --> 16:40.332
IF YOU DON'T WANT
ANOTHER WHOMPING.

16:40.416 --> 16:42.751
LET'S GO.

16:42.835 --> 16:44.086
(<i> both groan</i> )

16:44.169 --> 16:48.424
BE NICE, OR I'M GOING
TO START CRYING AGAIN.

16:48.507 --> 16:49.925
SO AM I.

16:50.008 --> 16:52.761
YOU ARE <i> SO</i> WEAK.

16:52.845 --> 16:54.805
OW!

16:56.390 --> 16:58.934
{\an1}OH, MAN, HERE COMES
THE GOON SQUAD.

16:59.017 --> 16:59.935
WE GOT TO SPLIT.

17:00.018 --> 17:01.186
COME ON, MACKENZIE.

17:01.270 --> 17:03.605
{\an1}WE'VE GOT A COOL THING
TO SHOW YOU.

17:06.775 --> 17:09.486
{\an1}LIEUTENANT RYAN,
WE NEED HELP.

17:09.569 --> 17:10.529
WELL, IF IT ISN'T

17:10.612 --> 17:13.699
THE TWO AS-OF-YET-UNCERTIFIED
JUNIOR LIFEGUARDS.

17:13.781 --> 17:16.452
STATE PROBLEM, NUMBER
OF VICTIMS, IN THAT ORDER.

17:16.535 --> 17:18.454
WE FOUND A LITTLE GIRL.

17:18.537 --> 17:20.079
{\an1}SHE'S RIGHT
OVER THERE WITH...

17:22.750 --> 17:24.084
DO YOU KNOW THE STORY

17:24.167 --> 17:26.878
ABOUT THE LITTLE BOY <i> AND</i> GIRL
WHO CRIED WOLF?

17:26.962 --> 17:28.088
NO.

17:28.172 --> 17:29.798
WELL, IT'S... REALLY VERY SAD.

17:29.882 --> 17:32.468
NOW, I CAN'T BE BOTHERED
WITH THIS FOOLISHNESS

17:32.551 --> 17:34.470
WHEN A REAL EMERGENCY
COULD HAPPEN.

17:35.763 --> 17:36.805
(<i> gasps</i> )

17:36.889 --> 17:37.806
(<i> wailing</i> )

17:37.890 --> 17:40.476
EMERGENCY STATUS, CODE ONE!

17:40.559 --> 17:42.227
OW!

17:42.311 --> 17:44.730
(<i> child continues crying</i> )

17:57.409 --> 17:59.077
{\an1}I'M HOT.

17:59.161 --> 18:01.663
AND I WANT
MY MOMMY AND DADDY!

18:01.747 --> 18:02.956
{\an1}OKAY, OKAY,
WE'LL FIND THEM.

18:03.040 --> 18:05.542
LOOK, JUST KEEP
WALKING A LITTLE BIT

18:05.626 --> 18:08.295
AND WE'LL GET
YOU A TREAT.

18:08.378 --> 18:11.882
I WANT A FREEZE-FREEZE AND
A SODA AND A PIZZA AND A SODA.

18:11.965 --> 18:13.300
YOU SAID SODA.

18:13.383 --> 18:14.843
I WANT ANOTHER!

18:14.927 --> 18:15.844
Lars:
LOOK...

18:15.928 --> 18:18.472
MAURICE HAS
A WITTLE GIRLFRIEND.

18:18.555 --> 18:19.389
LARS, CHILL OUT.

18:19.473 --> 18:22.351
MACKENZIE'S LOST.

18:22.434 --> 18:24.144
SHE IS,
IS SHE?

18:24.228 --> 18:25.771
(<i> teases</i> ):
OH, I'M SORRY.

18:25.854 --> 18:28.148
HEY, MACKENZIE,
GIVE ME FIVE?

18:31.276 --> 18:32.027
(<i> laughs</i> )

18:32.110 --> 18:33.153
(<i> shrieks</i> )

18:33.237 --> 18:34.029
(<i> grunts</i> )

18:34.112 --> 18:34.404
(<i> fist smacks again</i> )

18:34.488 --> 18:36.782
(<i> groans</i> )

18:36.865 --> 18:38.492
Twister:
COME ON, MACKENZIE.

18:38.575 --> 18:41.453
(<i> panting</i> )

18:42.412 --> 18:44.915
THANKS, LOSER.

18:44.998 --> 18:46.375
(<i> moans</i> )

18:46.458 --> 18:47.918
WE'VE GOT
TO FIND THEM

18:48.001 --> 18:50.879
BEFORE MACKENZIE EATS
THOSE GUYS ALIVE.

18:50.963 --> 18:51.922
I WISH I HAD A HELICOPTER

18:52.005 --> 18:55.592
OR SOMETHING
TO SPOT THEM FROM ABOVE.

18:55.676 --> 18:58.011
HEY, THAT MIGHT BE HIGH ENOUGH.

18:58.595 --> 19:01.139
(<i> panting</i> )

19:03.475 --> 19:04.977
ANY BINOCULARS?

19:05.060 --> 19:06.562
NO, BUT LOOK AT THIS.

19:06.645 --> 19:09.690
I DON'T KNOW IF IT...
(<i> bullhorn squeaks</i> ) WORKS.

19:09.773 --> 19:11.233
(<i> bullhorn squealing</i> )

19:11.316 --> 19:12.776
OH, I THINK IT DOES.

19:16.488 --> 19:16.822
HEY, BIG GUY.

19:16.905 --> 19:19.324
HEY, SHIRLEY GIRL.

19:21.535 --> 19:22.870
UM, WHAT CAN I HELP
YOU WITH, OFFICER.

19:22.953 --> 19:25.080
THESE ARE
LITTLE MACKENZIE'S PARENTS.

19:25.163 --> 19:28.542
SHE'S LOST,
AND WE'RE TRYING TO FIND HER.

19:28.625 --> 19:29.751
I'LL KEEP AN EYE OUT.

19:29.835 --> 19:31.587
MY KIDS ARE
AROUND HERE SOMEWHERE.

19:31.670 --> 19:34.089
IF THEY TURN UP,
I'LL HAVE THEM HELP OUT, TOO.

19:34.173 --> 19:36.133
Man (<i> over radio</i> ):
Shirley Company.

19:36.216 --> 19:36.675
This is Ryan at Tire 12.

19:36.758 --> 19:37.968
How do you copy? Over.

19:38.051 --> 19:39.928
ROGER THAT.
THIS IS SHIRLEY. OVER.

19:40.012 --> 19:42.514
A couple kids wearing goggles

19:42.598 --> 19:46.602
say they found a little girl
but did not have girl with them.

19:46.685 --> 19:49.104
Repeat: they did not have
the girl with them.

19:49.187 --> 19:51.815
{\an4}GOGGLES? SOUNDS LIKE
MY KIDS ARE WAY AHEAD
OF US, SHIRL.

19:51.899 --> 19:54.401
ROGER THAT. RYAN, OVER.

19:54.484 --> 19:55.527
Do you know the st...

19:55.611 --> 19:56.737
(<i> beeps off</i> )

20:01.283 --> 20:04.453
AFTER WHAT MACKENZIE DID
TO LARS, SHE'S MY HERO.

20:04.536 --> 20:07.080
{\an5}(<i> laughs</i> )
HE COULDN'T
EVEN BREATHE.

20:07.164 --> 20:09.082
MacKenzie:
AND YOU'RE NEXT.

20:09.166 --> 20:10.500
FIND MY MOMMY NOW

20:10.584 --> 20:14.129
OR I'M GOING TO CRY AND SCREAM
AND CRY AND SCREAM...

20:14.212 --> 20:15.881
WE'VE GOT TO FIND
REGGIE AND OTTO

20:15.964 --> 20:17.758
BEFORE MACKENZIE
GOES BALLISTIC.

20:17.841 --> 20:19.676
{\an5}(<i> chuckles</i> )
YOU MEAN, SHE
HASN'T YET?

20:19.760 --> 20:27.017
(<i> shrieking</i> )

20:28.727 --> 20:32.481
I AM TOGA MAN.

20:32.564 --> 20:34.274
{\an1}CAN I SING
YOU KIDS A SONG?

20:34.358 --> 20:37.569
(<i> cries</i> ):
I WANT MY MOMMY AND DADDY.

20:37.653 --> 20:39.029
I DON'T KNOW THAT ONE.

20:39.112 --> 20:40.948
MACKENZIE'S LOST,
TOGA DUDE.

20:43.742 --> 20:44.826
♪ I'LL SING YOU SONG ♪

20:44.910 --> 20:47.955
♪ OF A CUTE LITTLE GIRL ♪

20:48.038 --> 20:50.332
♪ THE SWEETEST GIRL ♪

20:50.415 --> 20:53.877
♪ IN THE WHOLE WIDE WORLD. ♪

20:53.961 --> 20:55.629
{\an1}MY TOGA!

20:55.712 --> 20:56.463
{\an1}PLEASE!

20:59.174 --> 21:00.509
(<i> toga cracks</i> )

21:00.592 --> 21:02.552
{\an1}(<i> screams</i> ):
MOMMY!

21:02.636 --> 21:05.681
WHERE ARE YOU?

21:05.764 --> 21:07.182
OH, WHERE WERE YOU GUYS?

21:07.265 --> 21:09.267
{\an5}WE'VE BEEN
LOOKING ALL
OVER FOR YOU.

21:09.351 --> 21:11.311
MACKENZIE'S
OUT OF CONTROL!

21:11.395 --> 21:11.853
SHE PUNCHED
OUT LARS

21:11.937 --> 21:14.439
AND DE-TOGA-ED
TOGA MAN.

21:14.523 --> 21:15.565
SHE PUNCHED OUT LARS?

21:15.649 --> 21:16.858
COOL!

21:16.942 --> 21:19.653
I'M SICK OF YOU FREAKS.

21:19.736 --> 21:24.032
WHICH PART OF "I WANT MY MOMMY"
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND?

21:24.116 --> 21:28.120
I WANT MY MOMMY AND DADDY
RIGHT NOW!

21:28.203 --> 21:29.871
YOU'VE GOT
TO STOP HER!

21:29.955 --> 21:30.956
<i>YOU</i> STOP HER.

21:31.039 --> 21:32.332
I'VE HAD ENOUGH!

21:32.416 --> 21:33.709
{\an1}WHAT ELSE
CAN WE DO?

21:33.792 --> 21:34.668
WE'VE DONE
EVERYTHING.

21:34.751 --> 21:36.044
DUH-- DAD.

21:36.128 --> 21:39.339
{\an1}WE'VE GOT
TO FIND RAYMUNDO.

21:39.423 --> 21:42.259
{\an5}Reggie:
HELLO! WHY DIDN'T WE DO THAT
IN THE FIRST PLACE?

21:42.342 --> 21:44.636
{\an5}Sam:
IT'S HARD TO THINK WHEN YOU'RE
AFRAID OF GETTING WHOMPED.

21:44.720 --> 21:50.100
(<i> screaming</i> )

21:50.183 --> 21:51.810
{\an3}HUH?

21:53.228 --> 21:55.814
RYAN, OFFICER SHIRLEY--
WE HAVE A BOGIE AT 2:00.

21:55.897 --> 21:57.357
(<i> screaming</i> )

21:57.441 --> 22:01.236
ROGER THAT. I HAVE VISUAL
CONFIRMATION ON BOTH OF YOU.

22:01.319 --> 22:03.030
RUNNING INTERCEPT COURSE.

22:03.113 --> 22:05.615
(<i> screaming continues</i> )

22:05.699 --> 22:07.701
OH, OH! BABY!

22:07.784 --> 22:08.702
OH!

22:08.785 --> 22:10.037
MY BABY!

22:10.120 --> 22:12.414
OH, WE WERE SO
WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

22:12.497 --> 22:14.916
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU GUYS LOST ME LIKE THAT.

22:15.000 --> 22:15.959
THE CROWD GOT
SO BIG

22:16.043 --> 22:17.669
AND YOU WERE
JUST GONE, HONEY.

22:17.753 --> 22:19.629
I'M SORRY!

22:19.713 --> 22:21.757
NO,<i> YOU</i> WERE GONE.

22:23.258 --> 22:26.136
CAN I HAVE A FREEZIE FREEZE?

22:26.219 --> 22:27.429
SURE. SURE, HONEY.

22:27.512 --> 22:29.514
OH, WE'RE SO RELIEVED
THAT YOU'RE SAFE.

22:29.598 --> 22:32.184
NOW, I THINK YOU OUGHT
TO THANK THESE GREAT KIDS

22:32.267 --> 22:35.103
{\an1}FOR TAKING SUCH
GOOD CARE OF YOU.

22:35.187 --> 22:36.521
THANK YOU VERY MUCH, YOU GUYS.

22:40.108 --> 22:41.401
{\an3}OOH!

22:41.485 --> 22:42.903
GIVE ME FIVE.

22:45.947 --> 22:48.909
AH-HAH, YOU THOUGHT YOU HAD ME.

22:49.868 --> 22:50.994
(<i> shrieks</i> )

22:51.078 --> 22:51.703
(<i> yelps</i> )

22:51.787 --> 22:53.622
(<i> screams</i> )

22:53.705 --> 22:56.416
(<i> all laugh</i> )

